================================================================================
2. BUNDLED STAR CATALOG — CC BY-SA 2.5  (HYG Database v3.6.1)
================================================================================

The `sky_stars[]` array in `src/skydata.c` is derived from the HYG Database
v3.6.1, © David Nash, distributed under the Creative Commons Attribution-
ShareAlike 2.5 licence:

    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.5/

HYG itself aggregates data from the Hipparcos catalogue (ESA, factual /
public), the Yale Bright Star Catalog (BSC5, factual / public), and the
Gliese Catalog of Nearby Stars (RECONS, factual / public). voidwatch uses
HYG's HIP id, RA / Dec / V-magnitude / spectral class / IAU proper-name
columns.

Changes made (per CC BY-SA 2.5 §3(b) "indicate changes"):
- Filtered to V magnitude <= 6.5 (naked-eye limit).
- Reformatted into the C `SkyStar` struct layout used by voidwatch.
- Spectral class column reduced to a single character.

The `sky_stars[]` data is redistributed under CC BY-SA 2.5. Anyone
redistributing voidwatch must keep the HYG attribution and the CC BY-SA 2.5
notice intact for that data section. Source URL of HYG:
https://github.com/astronexus/HYG-Database

================================================================================
3. BUNDLED CONSTELLATION LINES — GPL-2.0  (Stellarium "modern_iau" skyculture)
================================================================================

The `sky_lines[]` array in `src/skydata.c` is derived from Stellarium's
`skycultures/modern_iau/index.json`. Stellarium is licensed under the GNU
General Public License version 2:

    https://github.com/Stellarium/stellarium/blob/master/COPYING

Per GPL-2.0 §2, the *combined work* (the voidwatch binary linked together
with this constellation-line data) is therefore distributed under GPL-2.0.
That means anyone receiving a voidwatch binary has the rights granted by
GPL-2.0 over the binary, including the right to receive the corresponding
source code. voidwatch's source code is publicly hosted; that satisfies the
"source must accompany the binary" requirement.

Changes made: the polylines were transformed from JSON arrays of HIP
identifiers into pairs of indices into voidwatch's filtered star table.
Constellations whose stars all fall below the V≤6.5 magnitude cut are
omitted.

If you want to redistribute voidwatch under MIT-only (without the GPL
contamination), replace `sky_lines[]` and the Stellarium import in
`tools/gen_skydata.py` with a public-domain or permissively-licensed
constellation-line source.

================================================================================
4. JPL HORIZONS / SBDB ORBITAL ELEMENTS — public domain (US Government work)
================================================================================

The bundled comet, asteroid, and planet orbital elements come from NASA
JPL's HORIZONS system and Small-Body Database. As US Government work,
these are in the public domain. See CITATIONS.md.

================================================================================
5. CelesTrak TLE DATA — factual / attribution requested
================================================================================

The bundled near-Earth satellite TLEs in `satellite_elements[]` (ISS,
HST, NOAA 19, CSS Tianhe) were fetched from CelesTrak's GP query API.
Two-line element sets are factual numeric data derived from US Government
tracking; CelesTrak does not assert copyright on the numbers but requests
attribution for redistributors. See CITATIONS.md.

================================================================================
6. VENDORED STB_PERLIN.H — public domain / MIT-0
================================================================================

`include/stb_perlin.h` is by Sean Barrett, dual-licensed as public domain
(unlicense) or MIT-0 at the recipient's option. The file's own header
notice governs.

================================================================================
7. SGP4 ALGORITHM — public domain
================================================================================

The hand-built SGP4 propagator in `src/satellite.c` is voidwatch original
code, but the algorithm itself is public-domain (Hoots & Roehrich 1980,
Spacetrack Report No. 3) with corrections published by Vallado et al.
(AIAA 2006-6753) under terms that explicitly permit reuse. The voidwatch
implementation is MIT-licensed under §1 above.

================================================================================
SUMMARY
================================================================================

If you redistribute the voidwatch BINARY, you are redistributing a combined
work whose effective licence is GPL-2.0 (the strongest copyleft in the
combination). Provide source access. Keep HYG / Stellarium attribution
intact.

If you redistribute the SOURCE TREE without modification, the per-component
licences above govern each component independently.

If you fork voidwatch and want a clean MIT-only result, replace the
Stellarium-derived `sky_lines[]` with a public-domain or MIT-compatible
constellation-line source. The HYG star table can stay as long as the
CC BY-SA 2.5 attribution + share-alike notice survive.

For the full text of CC BY-SA 2.5 and GPL-2.0, see THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md
or the upstream URLs listed above.
